Computer Language: (("Teaching Languages" "How to Design Programs" "Beginning Student") (#(#t constructor repeating-decimal #f #t none) #f ()))
>Description:
"require" has become a lot more powerful and friendlier in the past five years, but the student languages have been completely left behind: they still have to use the horrible old syntax for planet requires, and they can't use "only-in", "except-in", "rename-in", "prefix-in", etc.

See PR's 10962 and 11025.
